  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through several approaches, including:\n\n1. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Regulations\n- Requiring financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n- Implementing Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Establishing reporting thresholds for cash transactions\n\n2. Law Enforcement Investigations\n- Specialized financial crime units\n- Collaborative investigations between agencies\n- Forensic accounting techniques\n- Asset tracing and seizure\n\n3. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Extradition agreements\n- Coordinated enforcement efforts\n\n4. Criminal Prosecution\n- Specific money laundering statutes\n- Pursuing criminal charges\n- Seizure of illicit proceeds\n- Imposing significant financial penalties\n\n5. Technology and Detection\n- Advanced data analysis\n- Machine learning algorithms\n- Blockchain tracking\n- Digital forensics\n\nThese strategies aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute complex money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.",
